Data from constant force experiments are represented by plots of extension versus time (Figure 8
). The measured sizes of the folded to unfolded transitions at 21–24 pN force are in the range of 10 nm–15 nm (for details, see Table 3
). Based on the known structures of other pseudoknots59., 60., 61. we estimate that the 3′ to 5′ distances of the folded pseudoknots to be approximately: 6(±1) nm. The lengths of single-stranded RNA were calculated from the WLC model. In the 21pN–24 pN force range, the conversion factor is 0.46 nm per nucleotide and leads to calculated changes in extension of: 11–14 nm (Table 3), which are in reasonable agreement with the measured changes in extension.
